cItpSccpTotalMsgs.name: cItpSccpTotalMsgs
cItpSccpTotalMsgs.reference: ITU Q752 Monitoring and Measurements for Signalling System No. 7(SS7) Network Table 9.
cItpSccpTotalMsgs.description: This counter is incremented every time a message is handled from a local or remote subsystem(Q752/9.3).

cItpSccpLocalMsgs.name: cItpSccpLocalMsgs
cItpSccpLocalMsgs.reference: ITU Q752 Monitoring and Measurements for Signalling System No. 7(SS7) Network Table 9.
cItpSccpLocalMsgs.description: This counter is incremented every time a message is handled from a local subsystem(Q752/9.4).

cItpSccpTotalGttMsgs.name: cItpSccpTotalGttMsgs
cItpSccpTotalGttMsgs.reference: ITU Q752 Monitoring and Measurements for Signalling System No. 7(SS7) Network Table 9.
cItpSccpTotalGttMsgs.description: This counter is incremented every time a message requiring global title translation (Q752/9.5) is handled.

cItpSccpUDTMsgsSent.name: cItpSccpUDTMsgsSent
cItpSccpUDTMsgsSent.reference: ITU Q752 Monitoring and Measurements for Signalling System No. 7(SS7) Network Table 9.
cItpSccpUDTMsgsSent.description: This counter is incremented every time a unitdata (UDT) message is sent (Q752/9 bis.1).

cItpSccpUDTSMsgsSent.name: cItpSccpUDTSMsgsSent
cItpSccpUDTSMsgsSent.reference: ITU Q752 Monitoring and Measurements for Signalling System No. 7(SS7) Network Table 9.
cItpSccpUDTSMsgsSent.description: This counter is incremented every time a unitdata service (UDTS) message is sent (Q752/9 bis.2).

cItpSccpUDTMsgsRcvd.name: cItpSccpUDTMsgsRcvd
cItpSccpUDTMsgsRcvd.reference: ITU Q752 Monitoring and Measurements for Signalling System No. 7(SS7) Network Table 9.
cItpSccpUDTMsgsRcvd.description: This counter is incremented every time a unitdata (UDT) message is received (Q752/9 bis.3).

cItpSccpUDTSMsgsRcvd.name: cItpSccpUDTSMsgsRcvd
cItpSccpUDTSMsgsRcvd.reference: ITU Q752 Monitoring and Measurements for Signalling System No. 7(SS7) Network Table 9.
cItpSccpUDTSMsgsRcvd.description: This counter is incremented every time a unitdata service (UDTS) message is received (Q752/9 bis.4).

cItpSccpXUDTMsgsSent.name: cItpSccpXUDTMsgsSent
cItpSccpXUDTMsgsSent.reference: ITU Q752 Monitoring and Measurements for Signalling System No. 7(SS7) Network Table 9.
cItpSccpXUDTMsgsSent.description: This counter is incremented every time a extended unitdata (XUDT) message is sent (Q752/9 bis.13).

cItpSccpXUDTSMsgsSent.name: cItpSccpXUDTSMsgsSent
cItpSccpXUDTSMsgsSent.reference: ITU Q752 Monitoring and Measurements for Signalling System No. 7(SS7) Network Table 9.
cItpSccpXUDTSMsgsSent.description: This counter is incremented every time a extended unitdata service (XUDTS) message is sent (Q752/9 bis.14).

cItpSccpXUDTMsgsRcvd.name: cItpSccpXUDTMsgsRcvd
cItpSccpXUDTMsgsRcvd.reference: ITU Q752 Monitoring and Measurements for Signalling System No. 7(SS7) Network Table 9.
cItpSccpXUDTMsgsRcvd.description: This counter is incremented every time a extended unitdata (XUDT) message is received (Q752/9 bis.15).

cItpSccpXUDTSMsgsRcvd.name: cItpSccpXUDTSMsgsRcvd
cItpSccpXUDTSMsgsRcvd.reference: ITU Q752 Monitoring and Measurements for Signalling System No. 7(SS7) Network Table 9.
cItpSccpXUDTSMsgsRcvd.description: This counter is incremented every time a extended unitdata service (XUDTS) message is received (Q752/9 bis.16).

cItpSccpLUDTMsgsSent.name: cItpSccpLUDTMsgsSent
cItpSccpLUDTMsgsSent.reference: ITU Q752 Monitoring and Measurements for Signalling System No. 7(SS7) Network Table 9.
cItpSccpLUDTMsgsSent.description: This counter is incremented every time a long unitdata (LUDT) message is sent (Q752/9 bis.17).

cItpSccpLUDTSMsgsSent.name: cItpSccpLUDTSMsgsSent
cItpSccpLUDTSMsgsSent.reference: ITU Q752 Monitoring and Measurements for Signalling System No. 7(SS7) Network Table 9.
cItpSccpLUDTSMsgsSent.description: This counter is incremented every time a long unitdata (LUDT) service message is sent (Q752/9 bis.18).

cItpSccpLUDTMsgsRcvd.name: cItpSccpLUDTMsgsRcvd
cItpSccpLUDTMsgsRcvd.reference: ITU Q752 Monitoring and Measurements for Signalling System No. 7(SS7) Network Table 9.
cItpSccpLUDTMsgsRcvd.description: This counter is incremented every time a long unitdata (LUDT) message is received (Q752/9 bis.19).

cItpSccpLUDTSMsgsRcvd.name: cItpSccpLUDTSMsgsRcvd
cItpSccpLUDTSMsgsRcvd.reference: ITU Q752 Monitoring and Measurements for Signalling System No. 7(SS7) Network Table 9.
cItpSccpLUDTSMsgsRcvd.description: This counter is incremented every time a long unitdata (LUDT) service message is received (Q752/9 bis.20).

cItpSccpCrToMtp.name: cItpSccpCrToMtp
cItpSccpCrToMtp.reference: ITU Q752 Monitoring and Measurements for Signalling System No. 7(SS7) Network Table 9.
cItpSccpCrToMtp.description: This counter is incremented every time a Connection Request(CR) messages sent to MTP. This count include ISDN-UP with embedded CRs (Q752/9 bis.5).

cItpSccpCrefToMtp.name: cItpSccpCrefToMtp
cItpSccpCrefToMtp.reference: ITU Q752 Monitoring and Measurements for Signalling System No. 7(SS7) Network Table 9.
cItpSccpCrefToMtp.description: This counter is incremented every time a Connection Refusal (CREF) message is sent to MTP (Q752/9 bis.6).

cItpSccpCrFromMtp.name: cItpSccpCrFromMtp
cItpSccpCrFromMtp.reference: ITU Q752 Monitoring and Measurements for Signalling System No. 7(SS7) Network Table 9.
cItpSccpCrFromMtp.description: This counter is incremented every time a Connection Reguest messages received from MTP. This count inlcudes ISDN- UP with embedded CRs (Q752/9 bis.7).

cItpSccpCrefFromMtp.name: cItpSccpCrefFromMtp
cItpSccpCrefFromMtp.reference: ITU Q752 Monitoring and Measurements for Signalling System No. 7(SS7) Network Table 9.
cItpSccpCrefFromMtp.description: This counter is incremented every time a Connection Refusal (CREF) message is received from MTP (Q752/9 bis.8).

cItpSccpRsrToMtp.name: cItpSccpRsrToMtp
cItpSccpRsrToMtp.reference: ITU Q752 Monitoring and Measurements for Signalling System No. 7(SS7) Network Table 9.
cItpSccpRsrToMtp.description: This counter is incremented every time a Reset Request (RSR) message is sent to MTP (Q752/9 bis.9).

cItpSccpRsrFromMtp.name: cItpSccpRsrFromMtp
cItpSccpRsrFromMtp.reference: ITU Q752 Monitoring and Measurements for Signalling System No. 7(SS7) Network Table 9.
cItpSccpRsrFromMtp.description: This counter is incremented every time a Reset Request (RSR) message is received from MTP (Q752/9 bis.10).

cItpSccpErrToMtp.name: cItpSccpErrToMtp
cItpSccpErrToMtp.reference: ITU Q752 Monitoring and Measurements for Signalling System No. 7(SS7) Network Table 9.
cItpSccpErrToMtp.description: This counter is incremented every time a Error Message (ERR) message is sent to MTP (Q752/9 bis.11).

cItpSccpErrFromMtp.name: cItpSccpErrFromMtp
cItpSccpErrFromMtp.reference: ITU Q752 Monitoring and Measurements for Signalling System No. 7(SS7) Network Table 9.
cItpSccpErrFromMtp.description: This counter is incremented every time a Error Message (ERR) message is received from MTP (Q752/9 bis.12).

cItpSccpCpcConfigLastChanged.name: cItpSccpCpcConfigLastChanged
cItpSccpCpcConfigLastChanged.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time of the last creation or deletion of an entry in the cItpSccpGttConPcTable. If the local network management subsystem is re-initialization, then this object contains the sysUpTime at the time when this occurred. This value can be used to prevent unnecessary walks of the Concerned Point Code Table.

cItpSccpMapConfigLastChanged.name: cItpSccpMapConfigLastChanged
cItpSccpMapConfigLastChanged.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time of the last creation or deletion of an entry in the cItpSccpGttMapTable. If the local network management subsystem is re-initialization, then this object contains the sysUpTime at the time when this occurred. This value can be used to prevent unnecessary walks of the Mated Application Table.

cItpSccpSelConfigLastChanged.name: cItpSccpSelConfigLastChanged
cItpSccpSelConfigLastChanged.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time of the last creation or deletion of an entry in the cItpSccpGttSelTable. If the local network management subsystem is re-initialization, then this object contains the sysUpTime at the time when this occurred. This value can be used to prevent unnecessary walks of the GTT Selector Table.

cItpSccpGtaConfigLastChanged.name: cItpSccpGtaConfigLastChanged
cItpSccpGtaConfigLastChanged.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time of the last creation or deletion of an entry in the cItpSccpGttGtaTable. If the local network management subsystem is re-initialization, then this object contains the sysUpTime at the time when this occurred. This value can be used to prevent unnecessary walks of the GTT Global Title Address Table.

cItpSccpAppConfigLastChanged.name: cItpSccpAppConfigLastChanged
cItpSccpAppConfigLastChanged.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time of the last creation or deletion of an entry in the cItpSccpGttAppTable. If the local network management subsystem is re-initialization, then this object contains the sysUpTime at the time when this occurred. This value can be used to prevent unnecessary walks of the GTT Application Group Table.

cItpSccpGttMapStateNotifEnabled.name: cItpSccpGttMapStateNotifEnabled
cItpSccpGttMapStateNotifEnabled.description: The SP linkset notification truth value. 'true' Indicates that the cItpSccpGttMapStateChange notification is to be generated when the state changes. That is, the notification generation is enabled. 'false' Indicates that the cItpSccpGttMapStateChange notification generation is disabled.

cItpSccpPrefConfigLastChanged.name: cItpSccpPrefConfigLastChanged
cItpSccpPrefConfigLastChanged.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time of the last creation or deletion of an entry in the cItpSccpGttPrefTable. If the local network management subsystem is re-initialization, then this object contains the sysUpTime at the time when this occurred. This value can be used to prevent unnecessary walks of the GTT Prefix Conversion Table.

cItpSccpGttConfigLoad.name: cItpSccpGttConfigLoad
cItpSccpGttConfigLoad.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time of the last load of the GTT table using file format.

cItpSccpGttConfigLoadStatus.name: cItpSccpGttConfigLoadStatus
cItpSccpGttConfigLoadStatus.description: The status of the current load or status from the prior load operation.

cItpSccpGttConPcTable.name: cItpSccpGttConPcTable
cItpSccpGttConPcTable.description: A table of concerned point codes.

cItpSccpGttConPcTableEntry.name: cItpSccpGttConPcTableEntry
cItpSccpGttConPcTableEntry.description: A list of concerned point codes.

cItpSccpGttConPcListName.name: cItpSccpGttConPcListName
cItpSccpGttConPcListName.description: The name of the Concerned Point Code list.

cItpSccpGttConPointCode.name: cItpSccpGttConPointCode
cItpSccpGttConPointCode.description: The concerned point code for SCCP GTT.

cItpSccpGttConPcRefCount.name: cItpSccpGttConPcRefCount
cItpSccpGttConPcRefCount.description: The reference count for this list.

cItpSccpGttMapTable.name: cItpSccpGttMapTable
cItpSccpGttMapTable.description: A table of SCCP GTT Mated Application (MAP) entries.

cItpSccpGttMapTableEntry.name: cItpSccpGttMapTableEntry
cItpSccpGttMapTableEntry.description: A list of SCCP GTT MAP attributes.

cItpSccpGttMapPc.name: cItpSccpGttMapPc
cItpSccpGttMapPc.description: The point code for GTT MAP entry.

cItpSccpGttMapSsn.name: cItpSccpGttMapSsn
cItpSccpGttMapSsn.description: The subsystem number (SSN) for GTT MAP entry.

cItpSccpGttMapDisplayPC.name: cItpSccpGttMapDisplayPC
cItpSccpGttMapDisplayPC.description: The MAP point code in display format.

cItpSccpGttMapDisplaySS.name: cItpSccpGttMapDisplaySS
cItpSccpGttMapDisplaySS.description: The MAP subsystem number in display format.

cItpSccpGttMapPcStatus.name: cItpSccpGttMapPcStatus
cItpSccpGttMapPcStatus.description: The GTT MAP point code status.

cItpSccpGttMapMultInd.name: cItpSccpGttMapMultInd
cItpSccpGttMapMultInd.description: The GTT mated application multiplicity indicator.

cItpSccpGttMapBackupPc.name: cItpSccpGttMapBackupPc
cItpSccpGttMapBackupPc.description: The backup point code for the mated Application.

cItpSccpGttMapBackupSsn.name: cItpSccpGttMapBackupSsn
cItpSccpGttMapBackupSsn.description: The backup subsystem number for the mated Application.

cItpSccpGttMapConPcList.name: cItpSccpGttMapConPcList
cItpSccpGttMapConPcList.description: The concerned point code list for the mated Application.

cItpSccpGttMapReRouteOnCong.name: cItpSccpGttMapReRouteOnCong
cItpSccpGttMapReRouteOnCong.description: The GTT Mated App re-route on congestion truth value. 'true' Re-routing on congestion is enabled. 'false' Re-routing on congestion is disabled.

cItpSccpGttMapAdjacent.name: cItpSccpGttMapAdjacent
cItpSccpGttMapAdjacent.description: The GTT Mated App Point Code adjacent truth value. 'true' Indicates that MAP PC is adjacent. 'false' Indicates that MAP PC is not adjacent.

cItpSccpGttMapLastSsUsed.name: cItpSccpGttMapLastSsUsed
cItpSccpGttMapLastSsUsed.description: The GTT MAP last subsystem used truth value. 'true' It is the last used subsystem. 'false' It is not the last used subsystem.

cItpSccpGttMapUsed.name: cItpSccpGttMapUsed
cItpSccpGttMapUsed.description: This counter is incremented every time a message is routed by the GTT Mated Application.

cItpSccpGttMapAltUsed.name: cItpSccpGttMapAltUsed
cItpSccpGttMapAltUsed.description: This counter is incremented every time a message is re-routed on congestion by the GTT Mated Application.

cItpSccpGttMapSccpUnavail.name: cItpSccpGttMapSccpUnavail
cItpSccpGttMapSccpUnavail.description: This counter is incremented every time a SCCP is unavailable at the GTT Mated Application.

cItpSccpGttMapPcUnavail.name: cItpSccpGttMapPcUnavail
cItpSccpGttMapPcUnavail.description: This counter is incremented every time a point code is unavailable at the GTT Mated Application.

cItpSccpGttMapSsUnavail.name: cItpSccpGttMapSsUnavail
cItpSccpGttMapSsUnavail.description: This counter is incremented every time a subsystem is unavailable at the GTT Mated Application.

cItpSccpGttMapPcCongested.name: cItpSccpGttMapPcCongested
cItpSccpGttMapPcCongested.description: This counter is incremented every time a point code is congested at the GTT Mated Application.

cItpSccpGttMapSsCongested.name: cItpSccpGttMapSsCongested
cItpSccpGttMapSsCongested.description: This counter is incremented every time a subsystem is congested at the GTT Mated Application.

cItpSccpGttMapMtp3Fail.name: cItpSccpGttMapMtp3Fail
cItpSccpGttMapMtp3Fail.description: This counter is incremented every time a the MTP3 layer failed at the GTT Mated Application.

cItpSccpGttMapRefCount.name: cItpSccpGttMapRefCount
cItpSccpGttMapRefCount.description: The reference count for this MAP entry.

cItpSccpGttMapCongStatus.name: cItpSccpGttMapCongStatus
cItpSccpGttMapCongStatus.description: The status of congestion level for this MAP point code.

cItpSccpGttSelTable.name: cItpSccpGttSelTable
cItpSccpGttSelTable.description: A table of SCCP GTT Selector entries.

cItpSccpGttSelTableEntry.name: cItpSccpGttSelTableEntry
cItpSccpGttSelTableEntry.description: A list of SCCP GTT Selector attributes.

cItpSccpGttSelTT.name: cItpSccpGttSelTT
cItpSccpGttSelTT.description: Translation Type (TT) for this GTT Selector.

cItpSccpGttSelNAI.name: cItpSccpGttSelNAI
cItpSccpGttSelNAI.description: Nature of Address Indicator (NAI) for GTT Selector.

cItpSccpGttSelNP.name: cItpSccpGttSelNP
cItpSccpGttSelNP.description: Numbering Plan (NP) for this GTT Selector.

cItpSccpGttSelGTI.name: cItpSccpGttSelGTI
cItpSccpGttSelGTI.description: Global Title Indicator (GTI) for this GTT Selector.

cItpSccpGttSelName.name: cItpSccpGttSelName
cItpSccpGttSelName.description: The name of the GTT selector.

cItpSccpGttSelNumPerf.name: cItpSccpGttSelNumPerf
cItpSccpGttSelNumPerf.description: This counter is incremented every time a global title translations is performed using this GTT Selector.

cItpSccpGttSelNotFound.name: cItpSccpGttSelNotFound
cItpSccpGttSelNotFound.description: This counter is incremented every time a global title title translations was required and a selector was not found.

cItpSccpGttSelQOS.name: cItpSccpGttSelQOS
cItpSccpGttSelQOS.description: The SCCP GTT Selector specifies the QOS.

cItpSccpGttSelRefCount.name: cItpSccpGttSelRefCount
cItpSccpGttSelRefCount.description: The reference count for this GTT Selector.

cItpSccpGttPrePrefConv.name: cItpSccpGttPrePrefConv
cItpSccpGttPrePrefConv.description: The Prefix Conversion Table is used to convert GTA digits. This object specifies that the conversion occurs 'before' global title translation.

cItpSccpGttPostPrefConv.name: cItpSccpGttPostPrefConv
cItpSccpGttPostPrefConv.description: The Prefix Conversion Table is used to convert GTA digits. This object specifies that the conversion occurs 'after' global title translation.

cItpSccpGttGtaTable.name: cItpSccpGttGtaTable
cItpSccpGttGtaTable.description: A table of SCCP Global Title Address entries.

cItpSccpGttGtaTableEntry.name: cItpSccpGttGtaTableEntry
cItpSccpGttGtaTableEntry.description: A list of SCCP Global Title Address attributes.

cItpSccpGttGtaTT.name: cItpSccpGttGtaTT
cItpSccpGttGtaTT.description: Translation Type (TT) for this Global Title Address.

cItpSccpGttGtaNAI.name: cItpSccpGttGtaNAI
cItpSccpGttGtaNAI.description: Nature of Address Indicator (NAI) for Global Title Address.

cItpSccpGttGtaNP.name: cItpSccpGttGtaNP
cItpSccpGttGtaNP.description: Numbering Plan (NP) for this Global Title Address.

cItpSccpGttGtaGTI.name: cItpSccpGttGtaGTI
cItpSccpGttGtaGTI.description: Global Title Indicator (GTI) for this Global Title Address.

cItpSccpGttGtaAddr.name: cItpSccpGttGtaAddr
cItpSccpGttGtaAddr.description: The Global Title Address is 8 octets of the Called Party Address (CDPA).

cItpSccpGttGtaAddrDisp.name: cItpSccpGttGtaAddrDisp
cItpSccpGttGtaAddrDisp.description: The ASCII display string of Global Title Address of 15 hex digits of the Called Party Address (CDPA). This object is deprecated so as to allow a null display string for a 'default' GTA.

cItpSccpGttGtaAddrLen.name: cItpSccpGttGtaAddrLen
cItpSccpGttGtaAddrLen.description: The number of hex digits in the Global Title Address of the Called Party Address (CDPA). This object is deprecated so as to allow a GTA address length equal to zero.

cItpSccpGttGtaSelName.name: cItpSccpGttGtaSelName
cItpSccpGttGtaSelName.description: The Global Title Address selector name from cItpSccpGttSelTable.

cItpSccpGttGtaResType.name: cItpSccpGttGtaResType
cItpSccpGttGtaResType.description: The SCCP Global Title Translation result type.

cItpSccpGttGtaResPc.name: cItpSccpGttGtaResPc
cItpSccpGttGtaResPc.description: When the GTA translates to a point code, it has a valid point code and cItpSccpGttGtaResType is 'pc'. Otherwise it is zero.

cItpSccpGttGtaResMap.name: cItpSccpGttGtaResMap
cItpSccpGttGtaResMap.description: When the GTA translates to a point code and an optional ssn, it has a valid point code and cItpSccpGttGtaResType is 'pcssn'. Otherwise it is zero.

cItpSccpGttGtaResAppGroup.name: cItpSccpGttGtaResAppGroup
cItpSccpGttGtaResAppGroup.description: When the GTA translates to an application group, it has a valid application group name and cItpSccpGttGtaResType is 'app'.

cItpSccpGttGtaTTorSSN.name: cItpSccpGttGtaTTorSSN
cItpSccpGttGtaTTorSSN.description: When this object is 'tt', the object cItpSccpGttGtaTTorSSNvalue specifies the SCCP GTT Translation Type (TT). When this object is 'ssn', the object cItpSccpGttGtaTTorSSNvalue specifies the SCCP SubSystem Number (SSN).

cItpSccpGttGtaRoutingInd.name: cItpSccpGttGtaRoutingInd
cItpSccpGttGtaRoutingInd.description: The SCCP GTT GTA specifies the routing indicator. When cItpSccpGttGtaResType is 'pc' or 'pcssn', this object has a valid routing indicator. When cItpSccpGttGtaResType is 'app' or 'as', the routing indicator is not applicable.

cItpSccpGttGtaQOS.name: cItpSccpGttGtaQOS
cItpSccpGttGtaQOS.description: The SCCP GTT GTA specifies the QOS.

cItpSccpGttGtaAddrDispZB.name: cItpSccpGttGtaAddrDispZB
cItpSccpGttGtaAddrDispZB.description: The ASCII display string of Global Title Address of 15 hex digits of the Called Party Address (CDPA). A zero length string specifies a default GTA value for the selector.

cItpSccpGttGtaAddrLenZB.name: cItpSccpGttGtaAddrLenZB
cItpSccpGttGtaAddrLenZB.description: The number of hex digits in the Global Title Address of the Called Party Address (CDPA). For a default GTA, the address length is zero.

cItpSccpGttGtaAsName.name: cItpSccpGttGtaAsName
cItpSccpGttGtaAsName.description: The Application Server (AS) name specified by the GTA. It is valid only when cItpSccpGttGtaResType is 'as'. Otherwise it is a zero length string.

cItpSccpGttGtaTTorSSNvalue.name: cItpSccpGttGtaTTorSSNvalue
cItpSccpGttGtaTTorSSNvalue.description: This object specifies SCCP GTT Translation Type (TT) value when cItpSccpGttGtaTTorSSN is 'tt'. It specifies SCCP SubSystem Number (SSN) value when cItpSccpGttGtaTTorSSN is 'ssn'. A zero value specifies that the TT or the SSN is not applicable for this GTA entry.

cItpSccpGttAppTable.name: cItpSccpGttAppTable
cItpSccpGttAppTable.description: A table of SCCP GTT Application Group Table entries.

cItpSccpGttAppTableEntry.name: cItpSccpGttAppTableEntry
cItpSccpGttAppTableEntry.description: A list of SCCP GTT Application Group attributes.

cItpSccpGttAppCost.name: cItpSccpGttAppCost
cItpSccpGttAppCost.description: The cost for the item in the GTT Application Group.

cItpSccpGttAppType.name: cItpSccpGttAppType
cItpSccpGttAppType.description: The type of the item in the GTT Application Group.

cItpSccpGttAppPc.name: cItpSccpGttAppPc
cItpSccpGttAppPc.description: The point code specified by the item in the GTT Application Group.

cItpSccpGttAppSsn.name: cItpSccpGttAppSsn
cItpSccpGttAppSsn.description: The subsystem number (SSN) specified by the item in the GTT Application Group. It is valid only when cItpSccpGttAppItemType is 'pcssn'. Otherwise it is zero.

cItpSccpGttAppRi.name: cItpSccpGttAppRi
cItpSccpGttAppRi.description: The routing indicator (RI) specified by the item in the GTT Application Group.

cItpSccpGttAppMult.name: cItpSccpGttAppMult
cItpSccpGttAppMult.description: The multiplicity of the GTT Application Group.

cItpSccpGttPrefTable.name: cItpSccpGttPrefTable
cItpSccpGttPrefTable.description: A table of SCCP GTT Prefix Conversion Table entries. When a packet with GTA is received, it may need global title translation depending on Translation Type (TT), Numbering Plan (NP), Network Address Indicator (NAI) and Global Title Indicator (GTI) present in the packet. To perform the translation a selector (cItpSccpGttSelTable) corresponding to TT, NP, NAI and GTI is used. The selector also specifies prefix conversion of the GTA before (pre) performing the global title translation or after (post) performing the global title translation. A selector can specify any or both (pre and post) prefix conversion tables. The prefix conversion involves matching of GTA digits in the cItpSccpGttPrefInAddr and then replacing those digits with the digits in cItpSccpGttPrefOutAddr.

cItpSccpGttPrefTableEntry.name: cItpSccpGttPrefTableEntry
cItpSccpGttPrefTableEntry.description: A list of SCCP GTT Prefix Conversion attributes.

cItpSccpGttPrefName.description: The GTT Prefix Conversion table name.

cItpSccpGttPrefInAddr.name: cItpSccpGttPrefInAddr
cItpSccpGttPrefInAddr.description: If the GTA of the Called Party Address (CDPA) matches the digits in this object, then the prefix conversion is performed.

cItpSccpGttPrefOutAddr.name: cItpSccpGttPrefOutAddr
cItpSccpGttPrefOutAddr.description: If the GTA of the Called Party Address (CDPA) matches the digits in cItpSccpGttPrefInAddr then this object is used in the prefix conversion.

cItpSccpGttPrefTblNAI.name: cItpSccpGttPrefTblNAI
cItpSccpGttPrefTblNAI.description: Nature of Address Indicator (NAI) for the Prefix Conversion Table.

cItpSccpGttPrefTblNP.name: cItpSccpGttPrefTblNP

cItpSccpGttPrefItemNAI.name: cItpSccpGttPrefItemNAI
cItpSccpGttPrefItemNAI.description: Nature of Address Indicator (NAI) for the current item in this Prefix Conversion Table.

cItpSccpGttPrefItemNP.name: cItpSccpGttPrefItemNP
